words.etymology_text: From Russian Кабарди́но-Балка́рия (Kabardíno-Balkárija), the initial part taken from kabardi

forms.form: Rare. Only used with substantive adjectives.

glosses: snug (small, comfortable back room in a pub)
cabinet (group of ministers responsible for creating government policy)

words.etymology_text: From Swedish kabinett, from French cabinet.

glosses: a cabinet government, especially one that is still subservient to a monarch

words.etymology_text: Internationalism (see English chabazite). Contains the suffix -iitti.
From Russian кабарди́нец (kabardínec), from Kabardian къэбэрдей (qɛbɛrdej).
From German Kabyle, from Arabic قَبَائِل (qabāʔil).

glosses: cabotage (right to transport goods or passengers within a country; in Finnish usually refers to an operator's right to transport within another country's borders)
